Notes: 'row_id' represents a unique row identifier, best mapped to the administrative case associated with the problem condition, as it likely corresponds to the case record rather than the patient or measurement.

The 'patient_id' directly refers to the patient linked to the problem condition, best mapped via the 'hasPatient' property to the Patient entity (Path 1). A 2-hop path was not available that better specifies the patient identifier.

'diagnosis_code' maps semantically to the 'hasCode' property leading to a Code entity representing diagnosis codes. Although 'hasCode' also leads to Terminology (Path 6), Code is more precise for a diagnosis code value.

'created_at' corresponds to the datetime when the record was created, matching 'hasRecordDateTime' property (Path 17). Other datetime properties like 'hasDateTime' or 'hasOnsetDateTime' are less precise for record creation timestamps.

'org_code' relates to the organization providing data, best mapped to 'hasDataProviderInstitute' leading to DataProviderInstitute (Path 8). No 2-hop paths provide more specific mapping for the organization code.
'org_name' is the name of the data provider institute, logically linked to the same 'hasDataProviderInstitute' path as 'org_code'. The institute entity would hold the name as a literal property.
